name: Jason Hudson
bio:
The Mighty Lass
Prince Edward County, ON

social_posts.post_text: Slice-and-bake cookies are annoying. But this is how to do it. Real-time video. It takes less than one minute.
Cookie Box 2022. 🍪📦
The Salty PB Honey Sablés from my newsletter the other day. Link in profile. When slicing a log of dough, give it a slight turn as you cut. It keeps everything cylindrical.
The 4pm light is right.
Looking to escape the monotony of these cookie boxes, I created a NEW cookie. The Buttermilk Donut Cookie. I’ll tell you about it in a newsletter soon. Sign up at the link in my profile.

75 🍪📦 are rolling out this week. So far my Chewy Chocolate Ginger Cookie has been the favourite. (Pictured here with @caseyelsass Black Cocoa PB.) You can find the recipe on my substack and make your own cookie box.
The statistical roundup. Details to follow on charities receiving donations. Honestly I haven’t decided and have simply been drowning in cookies. But many will benefit from your generosity! 🍪📦

The final batch of boxes is ready to deliver. 
•
And the final stats are in. 75 boxes this year contained:

85 batches
2625 individual pieces

64 eggs (5 dozen)
67 sticks of butter (17lbs)
80 cups flour (23lbs) 
8732g (19lbs) chocolate
8200g (18lbs) white sugar
6400g (14lbs) brown sugar
1kg (2lbs) peanut butter
3100g (7lbs) of rolled oats
After making thousands of cookies, you’d think I’d be done. But I made a new one. I’ll send out a newsletter soon with the details. Coffee Mint Meltaway. Intrigued?

Snowmageddon 2022 Update. It’s relentless. All the roads are closed. Huge drifts. Major winds. Thankfully we still have power. The horses had to go out briefly so @tjtasker could muck out the stalls, but they weren’t bothered. We are safe and warm and flush with cookies.
The Buttered Toast Cookie. The recipe will hit your email this week. Sign up in my profile. 🧈🍞

Storm of the century. It snowed for 36 hours straight. Big winds. Huge drifts. County roads were closed. But we didn’t lose power or a single tree. We’re lucky to live somewhere so pretty. The Mighty Lass lives on. (Vida and the Drifts by @tjtasker, slide 3.)

@KingArthurBaking announced their Recipe of The Year. They’re gonna release 10 coffee cake variations throughout 2023. I started with the Crumb Lover’s version. Extra crumb. The cake is light and delicious and there’s a satisfying chew in the topping. Recipes on their site now.
A banner year. Life on the farm. Dogs. Friends. Horses. Construction. Baking. Set to the inoffensive lobby music of an over-styled late-2000s boutique hotel. Happy New Year, y’all.
The 7 C’s Cookie nearly took my life this weekend.  But I’ll send a newsletter soon. Sign up in my profile. Tap for C’s. #jsnhdsncookies
Vida’s fav activity and why she sleeps 23 hours a day.
In your inboxes or at the link in bio now. The 7 C’s Cookie. Get at it.

This was actually the first recipe I developed, before all those cookies. A loaf using yellow bananas. It always seemed a shame you couldn’t have a banana bread unless you had black bananas at-the-ready. So I created one. 🍌🍞 Watch for a future email.
My Chewy Chocolate Ginger Cookie. Easily the most popular of the Cookie Boxes. The recipe is in an older Substack entry. Link in profile. #jsnhdsncookies
New cookie coming soon. Any guesses?
@TheWoksofLife Milk Bread. 🍞🍞🍞 Perfect. So squishy. Very easy. I’ll post a Story with a link.
Check your emails. (Or link in profile.) The Sticky Toffee Pudding Cookie is live. Pretty proud of this one. And brick dates? Heard of ‘em?
Deep winter. Still waiting for an electrical hookup at the new barn. It should happen soon. We’re closing in on a year since this ground was broken.
Squinting in the winter means it’s sunny and that means we can survive it. I miss @GermainCollinge in my day-to-day life and I like him on the farm, if only for an hour.
It’s a delicious dish, folks. Turn that sound on for the full experience. This recipe and more are on my Substack. Link in profile. And sign up for updates straight to your inbox. Thanks for caring.
Soon! Sign up in my profile to receive my newsletter.
Coconut Cream Pie Cookie Bars. 🥥 Will land in your inbox soon. These ones are wildly good and I’m super proud of them. Also, highly recommend the Kitchenaid Cordless Mixer.
More snow. 🐴🐴
Vida be nimble, Vida be quick.
I think maybe the best thing I’ve ever made. #jsnhdsncakes

I haven’t landed on a name for this cake yet. But it’s cinnamon toast and pudding chômeur and a stack of pancakes all at once and it’s really very good. Maple, rye flour, cinnamon, if you’re a fan of those things. 
•
I have it formulated as a single layer snack cake or this 3-layer beauty, so there will be options. Sign up for my newsletter and you’ll get the recipe sometime soon.

We’re very excited to have a fully completed barn. The electricity was finally connected and it’s perfect. 
•
Snow + overcast skies make for bright nights.

This girl doesn’t mind the cold. She eats ice and wants to romp around in the snow every day. But everyone has limits and hers is an understandable -21°C (-32°C with wind chill) She simply will not do it, even in her DOG FACE puffer and boots.
Moved the horses into the new barn today. 🐴🖤
This maple cake (in single layer or triple) will be coming atcha soon. #jsnhdsncakes
A few of my favourite things. A note on measuring spoons: Find a set that includes 3/4 teaspoons and half tablespoons and such. Very handy!!
Everybody needs a proprietary chocolate chip in their arsenal, right? 🍪 #jsnhdsncookies
There are several ways to groom a Norwegian Fjord horse. T.J. and his niece gave him this ‘do and it’s pretty chic, even with literal shit on his shoulder.

Mavic the 17’3 thoroughbred is back at The Mighty Lass. He’s adjusting well so far, but we’re taking introductions slowly. He’s enormously huge and seems bigger than he was when he left in December 2021.
Edd Kimber’s (@theboywhobakes) Oatmeal Ginger Slice. 👏👏
Getting close to sharing my Chocolate Chip Cookie recipe. With a Double Chocolate variation. 🍪 #jsnhdsncookies
Mo. Mobert. Moesha. Mogenshagen. Donkey. A rose by any other name.
Get a man who can do both.
One day he’ll catch a 🐀.
Made a Chocolate Buttermilk Donut Cookie outta my Classic. Go to the link in my profile and scroll to the Buttermilk Donut Cookie for updated info.
When the caffeine kicks in. 🐴☕️
ICYMI: My Cafeteria Chocolate Chip Cookie is up on my Substack. Look for the Double Chocolate Variation in the notes!  #jsnhdsncookies
Mav.
These cookies have smooth peanut butter, powdered peanut butter and almost a pound of peanut butter chips. 🥜🥜🥜
More snow. 🙃
If you were gonna make my Triple PB Cookies that I posted the other day, check the recipe on Substack again for the Double Chocolate Variation. 😵 Link in profile.
Exceedingly proud of this growing collection of original recipes. Swipe ⮕  #jsnhdsncookies
A glimpse of green(ish).
My Oatmeal Raisin Cookie is now up on my Substack. Check it out.
Working on my Carrot Cake, which jumps off my Short Stack Cake and uses the same method. Who doesn’t want puddles of spiced butter strewn throughout their cake? Recipe someday.
The weather clicked. The land is drying out. Soon things will sprout. It’s easy to forget how fast things happen when they start to happen.
This is what 3 horses on the grass paddock for the first time this year look like. Spring fever + horse power. It’s fun to see Mavic do what Mavic does. 🐎
I made a few mid-season cookie boxes this week. All original recipes. 🍪📦 Last slide is how I need to be after baking 6 dozen cookies and testing all my wares.
While clumsy, stubborn and domineering, horses are also the most tender-hearted. There’s nothing like it when one lowers its guard and nuzzles into you.
Spring springing. 🌿☀️
When you live with @tjtasker you get a beautiful roast chicken dinner on Saturday and Sunday leftovers is an epic hot chicken sandwich on homemade bread.
Barn-related content.
@WynneNeilly captured me and @MeredithPlant_ in our accidental coordination. Big Mighty Lass colour story.
That’s a Triple Peanut Butter Chocolate Chip. 🥜🍪
Only separated by like 1200lbs.
Big weekend vibes.
We’re building a fence around the new garden and we’re pretty proud of it. Learning new things in your 40s is fun.
The best girl.
Garden progress. 🌱🌱🌱@SproutboxGarden boxes assembled, filled and planted, fence posts dug and stained, galvanized mesh in place. To do: Mulch and gate building!
Some bird’s eye views of the farm today.
Garden updates. Wooden raised beds. Roses. A place to sit.
Black Cocoa Banana Bread. ⚫️🍌
Foggy Sunday.
A garden wander before a huge storm came in.
I built a 7 foot bench for the garden. My first attempt at mitred corners. Don’t look too closely. 📐
Made my first TikTok dinner. 🍔🌮 Impossible for this combination of foods to taste bad. Would eat again.
The start of this video is just 6 weeks ago. There’s a metaphor here about feeling encouraged. About being patient. About knowing the bounty is coming.
Sticky Toffee Pudding Cookies. On my Substack. Link in profile.
Working on a biscotti. Not my preferred cookie variety, but it’s recently come to my attention that people also like crunchy cookies. Cinnamon Almond. #jsnhdsncookies
Do you dip? Chocolate Coffee Almond Biscotti. Tweaking tweaking tweaking. #jsnhdsncookies

@MeredithPlant_ is Director of Florals at The Mighty Lass. She’s got phlox and foxglove and dahlias, zinnias and amaranth and yarrow. (And more.) After a weird slow start, everything is starting to happen.
The garden isn’t ready, but the meadow is bursting. Chicory. Sweet White Clover. Black Eyed Susans. Daisies. Grasses. Mustard. Queen Anne’s Lace. Curly dock. St. John’s Wort.

Banana bread in a Yorkshire pan.
Yuffins? 🍌
It’s the time of the year I take @BrianRieper into nature for his senior portraits. Come for the Forever Twink™️, stay for the 3 incredible gifs that close this carousel.

@pecishbaking.co is an absolute gem of the County. Their new expanded space is impressive and I cannot BELIEVE how much they crank out every day. Look at this gorgeous cube of raisin bread. Chewy and pully and perfect. 🍞
Big boy is feeling better after a lingering foot infection. Nice to see him … horsing around. 😏
The ultra-talented @MeredithPlant_ created her first arrangement from The Mighty Lass garden. Giant marigolds, sweet peas, phlox, amaranth, bachelors buttons. 👌
@MeredithPlant_ does it again. Soon she’ll offer arrangements for purchase. Stay tuned.

Garden updates. @TJTasker engineered a shade cover for the next round of lettuces. 
•
Nasturtium, zinnia, giant marigolds, yarrow and the garlic harvest.
Mere-golds. Choosing was hard. Swipe for more.

Working on a Date Square. It’s a Canadian thing. Dates on an oat base with a streusely top. It’s like a crumble meets an oatmeal cookie meets a Fig Newton. They’re ubiquitous here and every Grandma has her version. Mine is a close cousin to my Oatmeal Raisin Cookie/link in profile.
Summer on the farm.
The air changed today. Time to appreciate summer while it’s here.
@meredithplant_ is heading to @onewaltonshop to sell her beautiful arrangements today! Don’t miss it.
August is an august time of year. Is that where the name comes from?
My favourite parts of baking. Wet into dry. Frosting onto cake. Folding. Ribbony eggs.

Coming soon. The Peaches & Cream Sandwich Cookie. (My version of the classic Peak Freen Fruit Creme.) 
🍑
Peach jam with a shock of cider vinegar. Vanilla cream. Sandwiched between vanilla buttermilk cookies.
You can find the recipe for my Peaches & Cream Sandwich Cookies on my Substack.
Arranging flowers is a very specific and fascinating talent. I’ve been paying close attention to @meredithplant_ and can only hope to be a two-bit imitation.
More summer. Flowers. New fire pit. Friends. Dogs in thought.
I can’t let @meredithplant_ flowers perish in this 40° heatwave. If it’s hot for you, it’s hot for them! Bring them inside!!
Lemon Poppyseed Cookie. Soon. #jsnhdsncookies
Summmmmmer.
Adding hot peppers to flower arrangements since 2023.
September evaporated. The last slide is my Chewy Chocolate Ginger Cookie, but double-chocolated.
@jessiesheehanbakes Butterscotch Pudding. So simple, so delicious. An incredibly rich and flavourful pudding without caramelizing a damn thing. (From her book Snackable Bakes.)

I’m not sure when I’ll stop calling an iPhone a phone. It’s a small computer, but it’s  mostly a camera. I haven’t answered a voice call in 2 years. 
•
Selfies, dogs, Short Stack Cake with maple cookies, and messing with generative AI.
A flock of sheep. Two cabins. 3 ponds. 1 lake. 1 field of corn. And an old growth pine forest. All you need is 20 minutes and @Photoshop.
It’s been 30°C all week and I’m tired of it. Used AI to shove our yard into proper October. 🍂🍁
Lately.

I have covid! How quaint. And I don’t do much or see many, so it must be rampant in the community. An annual tradition at this point. 🦠
•
A retro and brief distanced hello with @seafoamgreg and @germaincollinge. Greg asked where he could get a cake and the answer is nowhere. So I made him one.
•
Back to the couch with my nursemaid. 
•
New earring season.
•
Remember when people washed their groceries?

Very excited to tell you my first recipe has been published over at @KingArthurBaking! My Sneaky Shortcut Banana Bread uses YELLOW bananas so you can have it anytime. Link in profile. Give the post some traffic, would you? And make the loaf and review it? 🥹
The most wonderful time of the year.
Your shopping list and reminder to make my Sneaky Shortcut Banana Bread I developed for @kingarthurbaking and then head over there and give it a review! You’d be my hero. 🍌🍞 Link in bio. 🫶
Moody.
Winter is coming.
November much?
@YossyArefi has a new book (Snacking Bakes) and I dove in with her Nutty Parsnip Cake. Like a spicier carrot cake. Recommend.

42.

Annual self-portrait to see what kind of mood I was in. Posterity, etc.
@CaseyElsass’ Shoofly Pie for @Epicurious. My first time making or tasting this Pennsylvania Dutch staple. It’s incredible.
Peanut Butter Chocolate Shortbread.

Still working on a Shoofly Coffee Cake - The flavours and vibes of a Shoofly Pie in a cake. 
•
Plus other various autumn vibes.
Made @cloudykitchen 30 Minute Thin and Crisp Gingersnaps and it made it feel like Christmas. (They’re linked in my Stories.)

When you visit @YearOfTheRyan he insists on making you the most beautiful, cinematic video. Here are my Chewy Chocolate Ginger Cookies all dressed up for Christmas. Link in bio for the whole recipe. (I will insist on black pepper in cookies until the day I die.)

Home and away. 
•
Annual @tjtasker pic at @LockyersCountryGardens. 
•
Swipe for a few 𝘮𝘰𝘯𝘶𝘮𝘦𝘯𝘵𝘢𝘭 pics from my 24 hour trip to Washington DC. It’s a bizarre place and I’m genuinely processing the kind of elaborate national pride on display there. But I was also extremely impressed by the feats of architecture. The Lincoln Memorial is at once restrained and also the same cubic volume as a Walmart store. America.
December has gotten away from me, so only a handful of cookie boxes this year, and none for sale. All my own recipes for the first time. 🫶🍪
Panettone is a hot trend this year. I’m in Cookie Mode, so made a tangy, citrusy sugar cookie with raisins and mixed peel. 🍞🍊
@nigellalawson Luscious Vegan Gingerbread. Incredible cake. You should make it. Happy Christmas!
@KingArthurBaking #recipeoftheyear is out and it’s a CCC made with browned butter and starting with a tangzhang yielding a tender yet chewy cookie. 🫶🫶🫶
Pretty, yet bleak.

The Mighty Lass
Prince Edward County, ON
